04 July
Regular Lines, arts residency REGULAR LINE SANTA CRUZ
California, USA  -  Santa Cruz
The project is the vision of Vlada Jakubikova of Boulder Creek and Zuzana Godalova and Julo Kristof founders of Nastupiste 1-12 based in Slovakia. It is a residency and exhibition program that gives an opportunity for Slovak artists to work in situ, exhibit their artwork and collaborate with the Santa Cruz art community during their residency in Boulder Creek, CA. The project is an adaptation of Regular Line program run by Nastupiste 1-12, a residency and exhibition program for Slovak artists to work in situ and collaborate with local artists in foreign countries and vice versa. First Regular Line was the Sheffield (UK) - Topolcany (Slovakia) cooperation with the British art organization Bloc Projects in 2013. Based on its success Nastupiste 1-12 adapted the project to include additional locations in year 2014: Regular Line Linz – Topolcany and Regular Line Topolcany - Santa Cruz. In this in situ project, 7 artists --- Erick Sille, Lucia Tallova, Veronika Sramatyova (painters), Matej Lacko (graphic designer), Lenka Srsnova (fashion designer), Zuzana Zabkova (performance artist) and Fero Kiraly (musician) --- will work in Boulder Creek near the Big Basin Redwood State Park. The Santa Cruz art community is welcomed to join the creative process, talk and take part in presentations and discussions. The final works will be presented in at the Apricity Gallery. Additionally, F. Kiraly and Z. Zabkova will perform during this year's Santa Cruz Fringe Festival. The artists have been selected by a competitive process and each is a great talent, spanning performance arts to music and contemporary art. Each artist has reached certain maturity in expression, and renown. Our belief is that these artists will be intrigued and inspired by the incredible Redwoods surroundings of the Big Basin area and the superb art community of Santa Cruz. The Slovak artists will be out of their elements. They have never worked in anything like the outdoors of Redwood forests. They will have an immersive experience in this fascinating world, and have a whole new perspective. Boulder Creek and its neighboring communities have an artistic spirit even among non-professional artists, and we hope and believe this will generate an incredible amount of access and diversity. Further, their entire creative process will be open. We will hold weekly presentations and discussions where the local public audience will be invited. Artists and members of the Santa Cruz community are welcome to watch, interact and be part of each stage of the creative process.


30 Jun
Király & Žabková REGULAR LINE SANTA CRUZ: PRED ODLETOM
Bratislava  -  A4
7 slovenských umelcov. 1 rezidencia. 2 výstavy. 5 performances. 18 dní na pobreží Tichého oceánu. 18 júlových dní strávia v kalifornskom Santa Cruz slovenskí umelci Erik Šille, Lucia Tallová, Fero Király, Zuzana Žabková, Matej Lacko, Veronika Šrámatyová a Lenka Sršňová. O export toho najlepšieho zo súčasného slovenského umenia sa postaralo Nástupište 1-12. Projekt Regular Lines vznikol v roku 2013 a v jeho pilotnom ročník vyviezlo Nástupište 1-12 trojicu slovenských výtvarníkov do britského Sheffieldu. V tomto roku sa projekt rozrástol a okrem ďalšej cesty do UK, predstaví Nástupište ďalších slovenských umelcov i v rakúskom Linzi a americkom Santa Cruz. Projekt predstavia osobne všetci zúčastnení umelci. Súčasťou prezentácie bude i predpremiéra hudobno-tanečnej performance Fera Királyho a Zuzany Žabkovej, „to (be) follow(ed)“.
20:00


